.TH "tiocsctty" 9 "tiocsctty" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tiocsctty \- set controlling tty
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tiocsctty
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "int arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
tty structure
.IP "file" 12
file structure used to check permissions
.IP "arg" 12
user argument

This ioctl is used to manage job control. It permits a session
leader to set this tty as the controlling tty for the session.

Locking:
Takes \fBtty_lock\fP to serialize \fBproc_set_tty\fP for this tty
Takes tasklist_lock internally to walk sessions
Takes ->\fBsiglock\fP when updating signal->tty
